---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const pageTitle = "Privacy Policy";
const description = "Privacy Policy for AuthenticNerd.com";
const lastUpdated = "February 18, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle} description={description} ogType="website">
  <div class="leading-relaxed text-inherit">
    <section class="my-8">
      <h1 class="text-navy mb-2 text-4xl leading-tight font-bold italic dark:text-white">
        The "Authentic Nerd" Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="mb-4 text-sm opacity-70">Last Updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      <p class="border-terracotta bg-navy/5 border-l-4 py-2 pl-4 text-lg italic dark:bg-white/5">
        "I value your privacy as much as I value my own system's uptime."
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="my-8">
      <h2 class="text-navy mb-4 text-2xl font-bold dark:text-white">What I Track (and Why)</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        This site uses <strong>AWS CloudWatch RUM (Real User Monitoring)</strong>. Unlike traditional marketing
        analytics, the goal here is System Performance, not user profiling.
      </p>
      <ul class="mb-4 ml-2 list-inside list-disc space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Performance Metrics:</strong> I measure page load times, JavaScript errors, and Core Web Vitals (LCP, CLS,
          INP).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Anonymity:</strong> Your IP address is used only to determine your general region (e.g., Newfoundland, Canada)
          to optimize CDN routing. Your full IP is never stored.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Storage:</strong> Small, functional cookies are used by the AWS RUM client to distinguish unique sessions
          for performance aggregation.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No Cross-Site Tracking:</strong> I do not track you across other websites. There are no "Like" buttons,
          ad pixels, or third-party marketing trackers here.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="my-8">
      <h2 class="text-navy mb-4 text-2xl font-bold dark:text-white">Privacy Browsers & Resiliency</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        If you use a privacy-focused browser like DuckDuckGo, Brave, or extensions like uBlock Origin, my performance
        monitoring will likely be blocked.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        This is perfectly fine. My site is designed to be a <strong>Resilient System</strong>â€”it will work exactly the
        same for you whether the monitoring script fires or not. I respect your choice to stay invisible.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="border-navy/10 my-8 border-t pt-8 dark:border-white/10">
      <h2 class="text-navy mb-4 text-xl font-bold dark:text-white">Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this policy or how your (minimal) data is handled, feel free to reach out via
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jerometerry" target="_blank" class="text-terracotta hover:underline"
          >LinkedIn
        </a> or check the source on
        <a href="https://github.com/jerometerry/authenticnerd" target="_blank" class="text-terracotta hover:underline"
          >GitHub
        </a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
